</bibRefCitation>
), was amended by 
<bibRefCitation id="7E454B16FFCC321EFEDC7AFD6833FD43" box="[307,567,724,749]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" refString="Litvaitis, M. K., Bolanos, D. M. &amp; Quiroga, S. Y. (2010) When names are wrong and colours deceive: unraveling the Pseudoceros bicolor species complex (Turbellaria: Polycladida). Journal of Natural History, 44, 829 - 845. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930903537074" type="journal article">
Litvaitis 
<emphasis id="28A0EAF5FFCC321EFE727AFC6BD8FD42" box="[413,476,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number id="AC1C24C0FFCC321EFE1E7AFD682BFD43" box="[497,559,724,748]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. These authors also studied the 
<emphasis id="28A0EAF5FFCC321EFC2F7AFC6E2BFD43" box="[960,1071,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">P. bi co l o r</emphasis>
complex through a molecular approach. It was observed that specimens treated as a single species in papers such as Rawlinson (
<number id="AC1C24C0FFCC321EFB0D7AD16F19FCBF" box="[1250,1309,760,784]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" value="2008.0">2008</number>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="7E454B16FFCC321EFAB47ADE6B56FC9B" author="Bahia" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" refString="Bahia, J. &amp; Padula, V. (2009) First record of Pseudoceros bicolor and Pericelis cata (Platyhelminthes: Polycladida) from Brazil. Marine Biodiversity Records, 2, 1 - 5. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1017 / s 1755267209000918" type="journal article" year="2009">
Bahia &amp; Padula (
<number id="AC1C24C0FFCC321EFEFF7B356B4FFC9B" box="[272,331,796,820]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" value="2009.0">2009</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
belong, in fact, to two distinct species with similar coloration pattern. The other species included in this complex is 
<taxonomicName id="DDD44D64FFCC321EFE8A7B166E1AFCF7" authority="Bolanos, Quiroga &amp; Litvaitis, 2007" authorityName="Bolanos, Quiroga &amp; Litvaitis" authorityYear="2007" box="[357,1054,831,856]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="rawlinsonae">
<emphasis id="28A0EAF5FFCC321EFE8A7B166881FCF7" box="[357,645,831,856]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">Pseudoceros rawlinsonae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7E454B16FFCC321EFD637B166E1AFCF7" author="Bolanos" box="[652,1054,831,856]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" refString="Bolanos, D. M., Quiroga, S. Y. &amp; Litvaitis, M. K. (2007) Five new species of cotylean flatworms (Platyhelminthes: Polycladida) from the wider Caribbean. Zootaxa, 1650, 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="2007">
Bolaños, Quiroga &amp; Litvaitis, 
<number id="AC1C24C0FFCC321EFC0D7B696E1AFCF7" box="[994,1054,832,856]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. We separated specimens in the 
<taxonomicName id="DDD44D64FFCC321EFA687B686AECFCD2" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="28A0EAF5FFCC321EFA687B686AECFCD2" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">P. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex by considering 
<emphasis id="28A0EAF5FFCC321EFDFC7B4C6884FCD3" box="[531,640,868,893]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">P. b i c o l o r</emphasis>
the ones without marginal line or with a thin line bright yellow to greenish at the worm margin, as indicated by 
<bibRefCitation id="7E454B16FFCC321EFD7E7BAE6985FC0F" box="[657,897,903,928]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" refString="Litvaitis, M. K., Bolanos, D. M. &amp; Quiroga, S. Y. (2010) When names are wrong and colours deceive: unraveling the Pseudoceros bicolor species complex (Turbellaria: Polycladida). Journal of Natural History, 44, 829 - 845. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930903537074" type="journal article">
Litvaitis 
<emphasis id="28A0EAF5FFCC321EFD1A7BA06929FC0F" box="[757,813,903,928]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number id="AC1C24C0FFCC321EFCD47BA1697DFC0F" box="[827,889,904,928]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Our immature specimens were of a smaller size (
<quantity id="DD2C9B02FFCC321EFF707B856AF4FC6B" box="[159,240,940,964]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
<date id="6E6A1027FFCC321EFF187B846B1EFC6B" box="[247,282,940,964]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">
x 
<quantity id="DD2C9B02FFCC321EFEE37B856B1EFC6B" box="[268,282,940,964]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" unit="mm" value="9.0">9</quantity>
</date>
mm) than originally described (
<quantity id="DD2C9B02FFCC321EFD6A7B8568D2FC6B" box="[645,726,940,964]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 mm</quantity>
<date id="6E6A1027FFCC321EFD327B84690AFC6A" box="[733,782,940,965]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" value="1915-10">
x 
<quantity id="DD2C9B02FFCC321EFD1D7B85690AFC6A" box="[754,782,940,965]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" unit="mm" value="15.0">15</quantity>
</date>
mm), but they agree with features reported in the original description and recent amend (
<bibRefCitation id="7E454B16FFCC321EFE017BE668D4FC47" author="Litvaitis" box="[494,720,975,1000]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" refString="Litvaitis, M. K., Bolanos, D. M. &amp; Quiroga, S. Y. (2010) When names are wrong and colours deceive: unraveling the Pseudoceros bicolor species complex (Turbellaria: Polycladida). Journal of Natural History, 44, 829 - 845. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930903537074" type="journal article" year="2010">
Litvaitis 
<emphasis id="28A0EAF5FFCC321EFDBB7BF86889FC47" box="[596,653,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="AC1C24C0FFCC321EFD7C7BF968D4FC47" box="[659,720,976,1000]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
